description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiatic Project Manager who will be based within the Emergency Department at Ysbyty Glan Clwyd, supporting a Nationally commissioned programme to support phase 2 of ‘What does good look like for the emergency department within Wales? ‘&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will support National Programme for Unscheduled Care in understanding &lt;em&gt;‘what good looks’&lt;/em&gt; like for patients accessing an Emergency Department and the creation of a National Emergency Department Quality &amp; Delivery Framework for NHS Wales (EDQDF), as well as the implementation of the Welsh Access Model (WAM). This will include work to agree care standards, a uniform approach to measuring activity and a nationally agreed model of care for Emergency Departments to enable optimization of clinical outcomes and patient and staff experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The National Collaborative Commissioning Unit (NCCU) is a national unit which is a provider of services to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Welsh Government in the form of the National Programme for Unscheduled Care (NPUC) which is a key National Programme sponsored by the Welsh Government, and it is currently developing a National Emergency Department Quality &amp; Delivery Framework for the NHS in Wales;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emergency Ambulance Services Committee (EASC), and it has created Commissioning Quality &amp; Delivery Frameworks on its behalf for Emergency Ambulance Services, Non-Emergency Ambulance Services and Emergency Medical Retrieval Services;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and it acts in collaboration with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the NHS Wales Shared Services Partnership-Procurement Services (NHWSSSP-PS) across the seven Health Boards, twenty-two Local Authorities and WHSSC for National Framework Agreements for external / independent (and commercially) provided care services covering Mental Health &amp; Learning Disability Hospital Services; CAMHS and Mental Health &amp; Learning Disability Younger Adult Care Homes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post would appeal to someone who:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;has recent project or improvement experience or a qualification that would support project management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;has ability to work with and quickly build strong relationships with a wide range of colleagues across health and social care organisations, and from fellow project officers to front line clinical operational staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;is motivated to make a difference to patient experiences; staff engagement; quality of care and delivery of value for money services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 22/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
